$ Avaloq: PL/SQL package obj_bgp#
@ obj_bgp#

Apparently, `obj_bgp#` is used to manage (start and stop) → Companies-Products/Avaloq/BGP[background processes]:
code {
begin
  obj_bgp#.stop; -- stops all running BGPs.
end;
/
code }

code {
declare
  bgp_obj_id number := …;
begin
  obj_bgp#.stop(bgp_obj_id);
end;
/
code }

code {

Restart a BGP again:
declare
  bgp_obj_id number := …;
begin
  obj_bgp#.valid(bgp_obj_id);
end;
code }

Alternatively, background processes can also be stopped (or removed) in *Central Services -> Background Processes*.
